# Switches which detector actively publishes geometry_msgs/PoseStamped on
# /aruco_perception/marker_pose — classical (aruco_perception's
# ArucoDetectorNode) or hybrid (aruco_perception_yolo_bridge's
# YoloMarkerBridgeNode). Handled by calibration_orchestrator_node's
# ~/set_detector_mode, which flips exactly one of the two nodes' "active"
# bool parameter true (and the other false) via the standard ROS
# set_parameters service — no lifecycle nodes, no process start/stop, both
# nodes stay running/subscribed the whole time. yolo_marker_bridge_node
# also keeps publishing cup_holder/hole detections_2d continuously
# regardless of this switch (depth-perception needs that stream either way)
# — this only ever affects the aruco_marker pose publish.
#
# mode: "classical" or "hybrid" — not a bool, so a third mode is never a
# breaking change to this service's shape, only a new accepted string value.
string mode
---
bool success
string message